title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Houston Astros on? TV, live stream for ALDS Game 4
text:
The Houston Astros can wrap up their American League Divisional Series win a win over Kansas City on Monday afternoon in Minute Maid Park.
Houston leads the best-of-5 ALDS two games to one.
Lance McCullers will try to get the job done against Kansas City while the Royals counter with Yordano Ventura on the mound.
The game starts at 1 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1.
Here's how to find Fox Sports 1 in Central New York:
Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
